目錄
Product Code: TC 2390Traditional network architecture is very complex and has some serious concerns like loss of data, static traffic flow, and increased latency rate. On the other side, software-defined networking (SDN) is dynamic in nature, provides increased network flexibility, and assists network providers in decreasing latency rate. Another big challenge faced by most of the network providers is how to connect the large data centers, because traditional networks do not support the dynamic requirements of server virtualization. SDN serves every business need related to networking such as centralized and distributed network architecture in local area networks (LAN), wide area networks (WAN), and in data centers.
SDN is creating efficient and effective networking environment in almost each industry vertical, but telecom and IT, and cloud services providers are the heavy adopters of it. In SDN architecture, any number of applications can be served by services providers and improve customer satisfaction. SDN architecture eliminates multiple layer architecture required by traditional network architecture by decoupling the control layer and provides virtualized control from a remote location. By using SDN applications, service providers can use proper bandwidth management in order to provide better browsing experience to end users.
The major restraints of this market are the security issues related to data transfer and lack of industry standard for SDN.
There are various assumptions that we have taken into consideration for market sizing and forecasting exercise. Few of global assumptions include political, economic, social, technological and economic factors. For instance, exchange rates, one of the economic factors, are expected to have a moderate rating of impact on this market. Therefore, dollar fluctuations are expected to not seriously affect the forecasts in the emerging APAC regions.
The report will help the market leaders/new entrants in this market in the following ways -

1. This report segments the market into solutions, covering this market comprehensively. The report provides the closest approximations of the revenue numbers for the overall market and the sub-segments. The market numbers are further split across the different verticals and regions.


2. This report will help them better understand the competitor and gain more insights to better position their business. There is a separate section on competitive landscape, including competitor ecosystem, mergers and acquisition and venture capital funding. Besides, there are company profiles of 10 players in this market. In this section, market internals are provided that can put them ahead of the competitors.


3. The report helps them understand the pulse of the market. The report provides information on key market drivers, restraints, challenges, and opportunities.
